description.narrative: In 2021, UNICEF accelerated actions to prevent childhood overweight with a focus on food systems. Five studies to strengthen policy framework were completed or are underway. A landscape analysis was developed to inform childhood overweight policy actions in Chengdu, while evidence from the pilot in Shunyi fed into a school-based nutrition campaign in Beijing. Children and adolescents were engaged in 11 policy dialogues to share their perspectives, and a report reflecting views of Chinese children was included in the UN Food System Summit and shared with the Vice-Minister of MARA and at the International Conference on Food Loss and Waste.;; | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:18/01/2022
